    "permit_type": "Land Use ReviewType 2 procedureHR - Historic Resource Review",
    "work_description": "Approval of Historic Resource Review for proposed exterior alterations to the Park Irving Apartments, which include replacement of existing aluminum sliding windows and sliding doors with vinyl sliding windows and sliding doors in the same style in the existing openings; installation on unit balconies (8 units) and in the central courtyard (9 units) of new air conditioning condensers that are enclosed in metal-louvered screening boxes; replacement of one garage door along NE 19th Ave with a new steel plate screen for a trash and recycling enclosure; and repaving of existing driveways, per the approved site plans, Exhibits C.1 through C.5, signed and dated 09/02/2025, subject to the following conditions: A.A finalized building permit must be obtained to document the approved project. As part of the application submittal, the following development-related conditions (B through E) must be noted on each of the site plans or included as a separate sheet. The sheet on which this information appears must be labeled \"ZONING COMPLIANCE PAGE - Case File LU 25-050496 HR.\" All requirements must be graphically represented on the site plan, landscape, or other required plan and must be labeled \"REQUIRED.\" B.At the time of permit submittal, a signed Certificate of Compliance form (https://www.portland.gov/ppd/documents/certificate-compliance-design-and-historic-resource-review-approvals) must be submitted to ensure the permit plans comply with the Design/Historic Resource Review decision and approved exhibits. C.No field changes allowed. D.Proposed sliding vinyl windows and doors shall have black frames and sashes, and they shall be installed within existing openings. E.Proposed mechanical screens shall be finished black.",
